defaultContacts.description: I am a Professor of Information and Computer Sciences at the University of Hawaii, Director of the Collaborative Software Development Laboratory, and the CEO of OpenPowerQuality.com.
I am originally from France. I maintain a list of reports from my surf sessions. I have proof that I ran the Hana relay with an actual Team.

Kim Binsted received her BSc in Physics at McGill (1991), and her PhD in Artificial Intelligence from the University of Edinburgh (1996). Her thesis topic was the computational modeling and generation of punning riddles, and her program, JAPE (Joke Analysis and Production Engine), generated puns such as 'What do you call a Martian who drinks beer? An ale-ien!'.

defaultSpots.name: Post Third Floor (IC SPACE)
defaultSpots.description: The third floor provides a study space available to all students who know how to sneak into the POST building past 7pm. Other than the fact that they barricaded the doors with state of the art locks, using the trick that I like to call, going AROUND the building, seems to do the trick. IC Space comes with a snack bar and tables outside if they're having their annual anime yikes meetings.

defaultSpots.name: Sinclair First Floor Study Space
defaultSpots.location: Sinclair Building (former library, 2425 Campus Rd, Honolulu, HI 96822
defaultSpots.description: The study space when you enter sinclair on the right provides tables for single use. The wifi is great and it is not cold.

defaultSpots.name: Library Second Floor Study Rooms
defaultSpots.description: Quiet, lots of resources, indoors, AC, private room, chalk board, you have to reserve

defaultSpots.name: Post First Floor
defaultSpots.description: You can only study in two study rooms. They are 126, and 127. For some reason they like to keep the lecture room open late, and security is chill about it. Good for meetings. 24/7

defaultSpots.name: Hamilton Library First Floor
defaultSpots.description: Quiet, lots of resources, indoors, warm

defaultSpots.name: Sinclair Second Floor
defaultSpots.location: Sinclair Building (former library, 2425 Campus Rd, Honolulu, HI 96822
defaultSpots.description: Quiet, lots of resources, indoors, warm

defaultSpots.name: Hamilton Library Second Floor
defaultSpots.description: Quiet, lots of resources, indoors, warm

defaultSpots.name: Sinclair Third Floor
defaultSpots.location: Sinclair Building (former library, 2425 Campus Rd, Honolulu, HI 96822
defaultSpots.description: Quiet, lots of resources, indoors, AC pumping, large tables for groups

defaultSpots.name: The Sunset Reference Center
defaultSpots.description: Quiet, lots of resources, indoors, air conditioning

defaultSpots.name: Library Third Floor
defaultSpots.description: Quiet, lots of resources, indoors, air conditioning

defaultSpots.name: Starbucks (not on campus)
defaultSpots.description: This starbucks is way better than the campus starbucks because the students walking all the way to this starbucks is trying to get some peace whilst studying. AC is good and tables are present.

defaultSpots.name: Japanese Garden
defaultSpots.description: The Japanese Garden is an amazing place. Quite, peaceful, and good for reading. However I'd suggest wearing some long sleeves if you don't want the bugs flying around.

defaultSpots.name: Glazer's Coffee
defaultSpots.location: 2700 S King St unit #D101, Honolulu, HI 96826
defaultSpots.description: If you're not into the starbucks environment but love coffee, Glazer's Coffee is the place for you. They have everything starbucks has but with less calories, and more bang for the buck.

defaultSpots.name: Center for Korean Studies
defaultSpots.description: They don't have tables but they have couches, indoors, and it is pumped with AC. The people there are nice with a clean water fountain, clean restroom, and clean floors. It's good for pit stops in between classes if you're on the outer rims of UH Manoa.

defaultSpots.name: Ban'an
defaultSpots.description: Enough tables for group study sessions, AC, good ice cream, and a bus stop right outside. It's walking distance back to campus.

defaultSpots.name: Art Building
defaultSpots.description: The Art Building is huge with tables right outside the main auditorium. It has access the largest restroom on campus with vending machines and a experimental fridge. Outdoors, crowd level depends on time of day, you might run into your friend.

defaultSpots.name: Campus Center Second Floor Starbucks
defaultSpots.description: There's a lot of pretentious hipsters that think studying here is the greatest thing in the world. The only good thing is that there's a lot of tables, good wind, and obviously, coffee next door. If you're going there to attempt to focus, you're out of luck.

defaultSpots.name: Post Second Floor
defaultSpots.description: For some reason the UH administration ran out of money to afford AC on the second floor of post so elitist engineering majors assimilate around the large tables. It's okay if you blend in though. 24/7.

defaultSpots.name: Stan Sheriff Center
defaultSpots.description: Good lighting, good AC, kind of weird though but if you know the faculty and staff they're pretty chill. Go to a bench and study up.

defaultSpots.name: William S. Richardson School of Law
defaultSpots.description: They got good lighting but lacking tables. If you find one though it's smooth sailing if you get a long enough extension cord for an outlet.

defaultSpots.name: Pieology
defaultSpots.description: A lot of people walking in and out but if you like white noise whilst studying it is a good place to go for lunch or dinner and get your work done.

defaultSpots.name: Paradise Palms
defaultSpots.description: Loud, A lot of people talking, a lot of table space though

defaultSpots.name: Music Building
defaultSpots.description: Really great if you know around the place, if you have access the music room and storage rooms there's desks with little to no people coming in and out after hours.

defaultSpots.name: Manoa Dining Services
defaultSpots.description: It's a chill spot to study with your friends or if you have down time in between classes. Not great if you're trying to focus. AC is okay. Noise is loud

defaultSpots.name: Dunkin' Donuts
defaultSpots.description: Dunkin' is located by Hamilton Library, inside Paradise Palms. They have the best morning coffee's if you love supporting American businesses. The noise can get a little loud but it's fine when you visit non-lunch hours.

defaultSpots.name: Hawaii Institute of Geophysics
defaultSpots.description: The Hawaii Institute of Geophysics provides enough tables for small groups or for solo studying. It does get crowded in between class times because there's nothing but lecture halls, but if you need a quick study session before class it is perfect.

defaultSpots.name: Saunders Hall
defaultSpots.description: Saunders Hall is located right next to QLC which has most UH buses going through it every 20 minutes. Saunders Hall has enough tables for single sessions. Outdoors, kind of hot, but it's alright if you need to focus on your work.

defaultSpots.name: Campus Center Stairwell
defaultSpots.description: Background noise, outdoors, sunny

defaultSpots.name: Campus Center Tree
defaultSpots.description: Background noise, outdoors, sunny, LOUD

defaultSpots.name: Shidler College of Business
defaultSpots.description: Background noise, outdoors, sunny, there's a snack bar but over priced, tables are dirty.

defaultSpots.name: Parking Structure
defaultSpots.description: Honestly, the structure isn't that bad. The wifi is good in certain places and it's great if you cramming for a midterm.

defaultSpots.name: John F. Kennedy Theatre
defaultSpots.description: Background noise, bus keeps driving by, no table space

defaultSpots.name: Campus Center Subway
defaultSpots.description: Background noise, smells, no table space

defaultSpots.name: Kuykendal Outside Tables
defaultSpots.description: It straight up sucks, tried it, never again. Actually bridge kid andy.

defaultSpots.name: Warrior Recreation Center
defaultSpots.description: For some reason there's half naked people trying to sweat on my laptop. They keep asking me if I could spot but the only thing I'm spotting is a top heavy built man with chicken legs.
